<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="158" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="158">
(male). Dorsal and ventral surface almost reddish-brown (Fig. 5b). Antennae almost yellowish-brown, antennomeres 
<normalizedToken originalValue="VI–XI">VI-XI</normalizedToken>
blackish. Legs reddish-brown to brown; tarsi paler than tibiae and femora. Head, pronotum, and elytra sparsely and finely pubescent.
</paragraph>
